question: At a local pet adoption center of dogs and cats, it is known that if a person adopts a dog or a cat, there is 0.45 probability that it is a cat and 0.55 probability that it is a dog. If a cat is adopted, the probability that it is a female is 0.6 and if a dog is adopted, the probability that it is female is 0.35. If a pet is selected at random such that it is found to be a male, what is the probability that it is a dog?

A factory has three machines producing bolts: Machine A: 50% of production, 2% defect rate Machine B: 30% of production, 4% defect rate Machine C: 20% of production, 5% defect rate A bolt selected at random is found to be defective. What is the probability that it was produced by Machine B?

On any given day in Lapu-Lapu Cebu, the probability of rain is 40%. If it rains, a weather app by DOST-PAGASA predicts rain with 85% accuracy. If it does not rain, the app falsely predicts rain 20% of the time. The app predicts rain. What is the probability that it will actually rain?

question: Which of the following is a true property of the Bisection method when solving $f(x)=0$?

options.a: It converges quadratically under most conditions.
options.b: It requires knowledge of the derivative of the function.
options.c: It guarantees convergence if the initial interval brackets the root and $f(x)$ is continuous.
options.d: It is faster than the Newton-Raphson method in all cases.
